Fish Creek is a small town with a harbor on Green Bay. It borders Peninsula State Park, a main attraction of Door County. The town feels much like a New England seaside resort or town
Most people enter the town by car
The town is compact and great for walking
There are plenty of shops selling all sorts of arts & crafts, furniture, and knicknacks
Numerous cafes sell food, many keeping with the town's seaside theme
